#   JS-004 [HIGH]: `len-1` / `factlen-1` `size_t` underflow on empty / zero-length strings

`JSStringGetUTF8CString` returns 0 on an empty string or failure; the `-1` sites
then underflow `size_t` to a huge value. Flagged by all 7 lenses (highest
confidence). Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  `JSStringGetUTF8CString` returns 0 on empty/failure. Sites subtract 1 unguarded:
    `convert.cpp:24-25` (`*idle += factlen-1`), `JABC.hpp:52` & `:64`
    (`varn[1] += len-1`), `io.cpp:430` (`u8sFeedn(..., len-1)`), `main.cpp:139`
    (`page[len-1]='\n'` → OOB write when `len==0`).
 -  `utf8.cpp:39` already has the correct guard (`if (fact<1) return BADARG`) —
    that pattern just needs to be applied at every site.
 -  `convert.cpp` is on the DEAD rdx path (unwired in `main.cpp:40-42`), but
    `JABC.hpp`/`io.cpp`/`main.cpp` sites are live.

### Goals
 -  Empty / zero-length strings flow through every path without `size_t` underflow
    or OOB access.

### Constraints
 -  Guard `len >= 1` before subtracting, mirroring the existing `utf8.cpp:39` check.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  (open) Apply the `fact<1 → BADARG`/early-return guard at each listed `-1` site.

