##  Outcome
 -  **LANDED `bd3a9c67`** (2026-06-16): guarded `len >= 1` before `len - 1` at the
    two LIVE sites — `io.cpp` `JABCioFileMap` (extracted `JABCioMapBuildPath`, now
    returns SNOROOM on `len == 0` instead of feeding a SIZE_MAX-underflowed,
    silently-discarded `u8sFeedn`) and `main.cpp` `JABCReport` `page[len - 1]`
    (`if (len < 1) len = 1;` removes the `page[-1]` OOB write). C++ harness row
    `run_mmap_underflow_repro` drives the path builder with `len==0/1/N+1`
    (RED before: `len==0` returned OK; GREEN after; ASAN/LSan clean). The
    `main.cpp` OOB is logic-verified (a 0-length JSC conversion is not
    deterministically forceable from a real JSString with a PAGESIZE buffer).
 -  DEFERRED to JS-014: `convert.cpp` (off-build) and the `JABC.hpp`
    `JABC_FN_ARG_*` macro `-1` sites (unused/pruned there).

